{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":844,"text":"When we think about prejudice and bias,"},{"time":3222,"text":"we tend to think about stupid and evil people"},{"time":5366,"text":"doing stupid and evil things."},{"time":7820,"text":"And this idea is nicely summarized"},{"time":9890,"text":"by the British critic William Hazlitt,"},{"time":12358,"text":"who wrote, \"Prejudice is the child of ignorance.\""},{"time":15293,"text":"I want to try to convince you here"},{"time":17405,"text":"that this is mistaken."},{"time":19040,"text":"I want to try to convince you"},{"time":20772,"text":"that prejudice and bias"},{"time":22495,"text":"are natural, they're often rational,"},{"time":25783,"text":"and they're often even moral,"},{"time":27614,"text":"and I think that once we understand this,"},{"time":29866,"text":"we're in a better position to make sense of them"},{"time":32375,"text":"when they go wrong,"},{"time":33432,"text":"when they have horrible consequences,"},{"time":35200,"text":"and we're in a better position to know what to do"},{"time":37525,"text":"when this happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39207,"text":"So, start with stereotypes. You look at me,"},{"time":42234,"text":"you know my name, you\nknow certain facts about me,"},{"time":44480,"text":"and you could make certain judgments."},{"time":46309,"text":"You could make guesses about my ethnicity,"},{"time":49162,"text":"my political affiliation, my religious beliefs."},{"time":52443,"text":"And the thing is, these\njudgments tend to be accurate."},{"time":54542,"text":"We're very good at this sort of thing."},{"time":56724,"text":"And we're very good at this sort of thing"},{"time":58207,"text":"because our ability to stereotype people"},{"time":60940,"text":"is not some sort of arbitrary quirk of the mind,"},{"time":64195,"text":"but rather it's a specific instance"},{"time":66511,"text":"of a more general process,"},{"time":68166,"text":"which is that we have experience"},{"time":69785,"text":"with things and people in the world"},{"time":71326,"text":"that fall into categories,"},{"time":72575,"text":"and we can use our experience\nto make generalizations"},{"time":75031,"text":"about novel instances of these categories."},{"time":77390,"text":"So everybody here has a lot of experience"},{"time":79757,"text":"with chairs and apples and dogs,"},{"time":82010,"text":"and based on this, you could see"},{"time":83646,"text":"unfamiliar examples and you could guess,"},{"time":85998,"text":"you could sit on the chair,"},{"time":87314,"text":"you could eat the apple, the dog will bark."},{"time":89879,"text":"Now we might be wrong."},{"time":91643,"text":"The chair could collapse if you sit on it,"},{"time":93443,"text":"the apple might be poison, the dog might not bark,"},{"time":95665,"text":"and in fact, this is my dog Tessie, who doesn't bark."},{"time":98535,"text":"But for the most part, we're good at this."},{"time":101294,"text":"For the most part, we make good guesses"},{"time":103210,"text":"both in the social domain and the non-social domain,"},{"time":105024,"text":"and if we weren't able to do so,"},{"time":106973,"text":"if we weren't able to make guesses about\nnew instances that we encounter,"},{"time":110189,"text":"we wouldn't survive."},{"time":111640,"text":"And in fact, Hazlitt later on in his wonderful essay"},{"time":114509,"text":"concedes this."},{"time":115994,"text":"He writes, \"Without the aid of prejudice and custom,"},{"time":118536,"text":"I should not be able to find\nmy way my across the room;"},{"time":120876,"text":"nor know how to conduct\nmyself in any circumstances,"},{"time":123328,"text":"nor what to feel in any relation of life.\""},{"time":127531,"text":"Or take bias."},{"time":129040,"text":"Now sometimes, we break the world up into"},{"time":130748,"text":"us versus them, into in-group versus out-group,"},{"time":133749,"text":"and sometimes when we do this,"},{"time":134910,"text":"we know we're doing something wrong,"},{"time":136467,"text":"and we're kind of ashamed of it."},{"time":138140,"text":"But other times we're proud of it."},{"time":139623,"text":"We openly acknowledge it."},{"time":141436,"text":"And my favorite example of this"},{"time":142718,"text":"is a question that came from the audience"},{"time":145120,"text":"in a Republican debate prior to the last election."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147837,"text":"(Video) Anderson Cooper: Gets to your question,"},{"time":150129,"text":"the question in the hall, on foreign aid? Yes, ma'am."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154310,"text":"Woman: The American people are suffering"},{"time":156546,"text":"in our country right now."},{"time":159183,"text":"Why do we continue to send foreign aid"},{"time":162531,"text":"to other countries"},{"time":163847,"text":"when we need all the help we can get for ourselves?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":167950,"text":"AC: Governor Perry, what about that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":169645,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":171012,"text":"Rick Perry: Absolutely, I think it's—"}]},{"cues":[{"time":173350,"text":"Paul Bloom: Each of the people onstage"},{"time":175010,"text":"agreed with the premise of her question,"},{"time":176981,"text":"which is as Americans, we should care more"},{"time":179100,"text":"about Americans than about other people."},{"time":181226,"text":"And in fact, in general, people are often swayed"},{"time":184091,"text":"by feelings of solidarity, loyalty, pride, patriotism,"},{"time":187599,"text":"towards their country or towards their ethnic group."},{"time":190315,"text":"Regardless of your politics, many\npeople feel proud to be American,"},{"time":193400,"text":"and they favor Americans over other countries."},{"time":195462,"text":"Residents of other countries\nfeel the same about their nation,"},{"time":198312,"text":"and we feel the same about our ethnicities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200798,"text":"Now some of you may reject this."},{"time":202482,"text":"Some of you may be so cosmopolitan"},{"time":204213,"text":"that you think that ethnicity and nationality"},{"time":206547,"text":"should hold no moral sway."},{"time":208700,"text":"But even you sophisticates accept"},{"time":211462,"text":"that there should be some pull"},{"time":213296,"text":"towards the in-group in the\ndomain of friends and family,"},{"time":215997,"text":"of people you're close to,"},{"time":217418,"text":"and so even you make a distinction"},{"time":218979,"text":"between us versus them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220954,"text":"Now, this distinction is natural enough"},{"time":223557,"text":"and often moral enough, but it can go awry,"},{"time":226481,"text":"and this was part of the research"},{"time":228210,"text":"of the great social psychologist Henri Tajfel."},{"time":230969,"text":"Tajfel was born in Poland in 1919."},{"time":233574,"text":"He left to go to university in France,"},{"time":235713,"text":"because as a Jew, he couldn't\ngo to university in Poland,"},{"time":238268,"text":"and then he enlisted in the French military"},{"time":240778,"text":"in World War II."},{"time":242061,"text":"He was captured and ended up"},{"time":243830,"text":"in a prisoner of war camp,"},{"time":245361,"text":"and it was a terrifying time for him,"},{"time":247628,"text":"because if it was discovered that he was a Jew,"},{"time":249316,"text":"he could have been moved to a concentration camp,"},{"time":251408,"text":"where he most likely would not have survived."},{"time":253400,"text":"And in fact, when the war\nended and he was released,"},{"time":255987,"text":"most of his friends and family were dead."},{"time":258492,"text":"He got involved in different pursuits."},{"time":260329,"text":"He helped out the war orphans."},{"time":261860,"text":"But he had a long-lasting interest"},{"time":263591,"text":"in the science of prejudice,"},{"time":265136,"text":"and so when a prestigious British scholarship"},{"time":267796,"text":"on stereotypes opened up, he applied for it,"},{"time":269641,"text":"and he won it,"},{"time":270998,"text":"and then he began this amazing career."},{"time":273188,"text":"And what started his career is an insight"},{"time":275937,"text":"that the way most people were thinking"},{"time":277777,"text":"about the Holocaust was wrong."},{"time":279893,"text":"Many people, most people at the time,"},{"time":282299,"text":"viewed the Holocaust as sort of representing"},{"time":284200,"text":"some tragic flaw on the part of the Germans,"},{"time":287204,"text":"some genetic taint, some authoritarian personality."},{"time":291038,"text":"And Tajfel rejected this."},{"time":293096,"text":"Tajfel said what we see in the Holocaust"},{"time":295639,"text":"is just an exaggeration"},{"time":297950,"text":"of normal psychological processes"},{"time":299728,"text":"that exist in every one of us."},{"time":301489,"text":"And to explore this, he did a series of classic studies"},{"time":304174,"text":"with British adolescents."},{"time":305918,"text":"And in one of his studies, what he did was he asked"},{"time":307467,"text":"the British adolescents all sorts of questions,"},{"time":310019,"text":"and then based on their answers, he said,"},{"time":311903,"text":"\"I've looked at your answers,\nand based on the answers,"},{"time":314260,"text":"I have determined that you are either\" —"},{"time":316357,"text":"he told half of them —"},{"time":317363,"text":"\"a Kandinsky lover, you love the work of Kandinsky,"},{"time":320320,"text":"or a Klee lover, you love the work of Klee.\""},{"time":323298,"text":"It was entirely bogus."},{"time":325114,"text":"Their answers had nothing\nto do with Kandinsky or Klee."},{"time":327404,"text":"They probably hadn't heard of the artists."},{"time":330132,"text":"He just arbitrarily divided them up."},{"time":332872,"text":"But what he found was, these categories mattered,"},{"time":336143,"text":"so when he later gave the subjects money,"},{"time":338654,"text":"they would prefer to give the money"},{"time":340330,"text":"to members of their own group"},{"time":342130,"text":"than members of the other group."},{"time":343963,"text":"Worse, they were actually most interested"},{"time":346290,"text":"in establishing a difference"},{"time":348296,"text":"between their group and other groups,"},{"time":350862,"text":"so they would give up money for their own group"},{"time":352770,"text":"if by doing so they could give\nthe other group even less."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358018,"text":"This bias seems to show up very early."},{"time":360236,"text":"So my colleague and wife, Karen Wynn, at Yale"},{"time":362536,"text":"has done a series of studies with babies"},{"time":364147,"text":"where she exposes babies to puppets,"},{"time":366979,"text":"and the puppets have certain food preferences."},{"time":369244,"text":"So one of the puppets might like green beans."},{"time":371426,"text":"The other puppet might like graham crackers."},{"time":374001,"text":"They test the babies own food preferences,"},{"time":376370,"text":"and babies typically prefer the graham crackers."},{"time":379060,"text":"But the question is, does this matter to babies"},{"time":381672,"text":"in how they treat the puppets? And it matters a lot."},{"time":384788,"text":"They tend to prefer the puppet"},{"time":386307,"text":"who has the same food tastes that they have,"},{"time":389786,"text":"and worse, they actually prefer puppets"},{"time":392342,"text":"who punish the puppet with the different food taste."},{"time":395327,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":397604,"text":"We see this sort of in-group,\nout-group psychology all the time."},{"time":401236,"text":"We see it in political clashes"},{"time":402900,"text":"within groups with different ideologies."},{"time":405314,"text":"We see it in its extreme in cases of war,"},{"time":408940,"text":"where the out-group isn't merely given less,"},{"time":412157,"text":"but dehumanized,"},{"time":413745,"text":"as in the Nazi perspective of Jews"},{"time":415985,"text":"as vermin or lice,"},{"time":418070,"text":"or the American perspective of Japanese as rats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422306,"text":"Stereotypes can also go awry."},{"time":424520,"text":"So often they're rational and useful,"},{"time":426781,"text":"but sometimes they're irrational,"},{"time":428355,"text":"they give the wrong answers,"},{"time":429581,"text":"and other times"},{"time":430798,"text":"they lead to plainly immoral consequences."},{"time":432973,"text":"And the case that's been most studied"},{"time":435781,"text":"is the case of race."},{"time":437448,"text":"There was a fascinating study"},{"time":438855,"text":"prior to the 2008 election"},{"time":440929,"text":"where social psychologists looked at the extent"},{"time":443955,"text":"to which the candidates were\nassociated with America,"},{"time":447397,"text":"as in an unconscious association\nwith the American flag."},{"time":451002,"text":"And in one of their studies they compared"},{"time":452358,"text":"Obama and McCain, and they found McCain"},{"time":454372,"text":"is thought of as more American than Obama,"},{"time":457766,"text":"and to some extent, people aren't \nthat surprised by hearing that."},{"time":460339,"text":"McCain is a celebrated war hero,"},{"time":462257,"text":"and many people would explicitly say"},{"time":463916,"text":"he has more of an American story than Obama."},{"time":466616,"text":"But they also compared Obama"},{"time":468553,"text":"to British Prime Minister Tony Blair,"},{"time":471069,"text":"and they found that Blair was also thought of"},{"time":473330,"text":"as more American than Obama,"},{"time":475837,"text":"even though subjects explicitly understood"},{"time":477910,"text":"that he's not American at all."},{"time":480900,"text":"But they were responding, of course,"},{"time":482324,"text":"to the color of his skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485375,"text":"These stereotypes and biases"},{"time":487426,"text":"have real-world consequences,"},{"time":488876,"text":"both subtle and very important."},{"time":491748,"text":"In one recent study, researchers"},{"time":494410,"text":"put ads on eBay for the sale of baseball cards."},{"time":497679,"text":"Some of them were held by white hands,"},{"time":500413,"text":"others by black hands."},{"time":501631,"text":"They were the same baseball cards."},{"time":503210,"text":"The ones held by black hands"},{"time":504454,"text":"got substantially smaller bids"},{"time":506521,"text":"than the ones held by white hands."},{"time":509005,"text":"In research done at Stanford,"},{"time":511367,"text":"psychologists explored the case of people"},{"time":515597,"text":"sentenced for the murder of a white person."},{"time":519166,"text":"It turns out, holding everything else constant,"},{"time":521970,"text":"you are considerably more likely to be executed"},{"time":524340,"text":"if you look like the man on the right"},{"time":526117,"text":"than the man on the left,"},{"time":528090,"text":"and this is in large part because"},{"time":530119,"text":"the man on the right looks more prototypically black,"},{"time":532653,"text":"more prototypically African-American,"},{"time":535283,"text":"and this apparently influences people's decisions"},{"time":537332,"text":"over what to do about him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539103,"text":"So now that we know about this,"},{"time":540650,"text":"how do we combat it?"},{"time":542307,"text":"And there are different avenues."},{"time":543929,"text":"One avenue is to appeal"},{"time":545363,"text":"to people's emotional responses,"},{"time":547409,"text":"to appeal to people's empathy,"},{"time":549542,"text":"and we often do that through stories."},{"time":551415,"text":"So if you are a liberal parent"},{"time":553980,"text":"and you want to encourage your children"},{"time":555852,"text":"to believe in the merits of nontraditional families,"},{"time":558226,"text":"you might give them a book like this.\n[\"Heather Has Two Mommies\"]"},{"time":560499,"text":"If you are conservative and have a different attitude,"},{"time":562225,"text":"you might give them a book like this."},{"time":564156,"text":"(Laughter)\n[\"Help! Mom! There Are Liberals under My Bed!\"]"},{"time":565905,"text":"But in general, stories can turn"},{"time":569241,"text":"anonymous strangers into people who matter,"},{"time":571473,"text":"and the idea that we care about people"},{"time":574158,"text":"when we focus on them as individuals"},{"time":575860,"text":"is an idea which has shown up across history."},{"time":578139,"text":"So Stalin apocryphally said,"},{"time":580722,"text":"\"A single death is a tragedy,"},{"time":582339,"text":"a million deaths is a statistic,\""},{"time":584379,"text":"and Mother Teresa said,"},{"time":585830,"text":"\"If I look at the mass, I will never act."},{"time":587371,"text":"If I look at the one, I will.\""},{"time":589696,"text":"Psychologists have explored this."},{"time":591766,"text":"For instance, in one study,"},{"time":593067,"text":"people were given a list of facts about a crisis,"},{"time":595850,"text":"and it was seen how much they would donate"},{"time":600106,"text":"to solve this crisis,"},{"time":601690,"text":"and another group was given no facts at all"},{"time":603527,"text":"but they were told of an individual"},{"time":605625,"text":"and given a name and given a face,"},{"time":608065,"text":"and it turns out that they gave far more."},{"time":611284,"text":"None of this I think is a secret"},{"time":613145,"text":"to the people who are engaged in charity work."},{"time":615256,"text":"People don't tend to deluge people"},{"time":617904,"text":"with facts and statistics."},{"time":619227,"text":"Rather, you show them faces,"},{"time":620249,"text":"you show them people."},{"time":621985,"text":"It's possible that by extending our sympathies"},{"time":625212,"text":"to an individual, they can spread"},{"time":627183,"text":"to the group that the individual belongs to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630061,"text":"This is Harriet Beecher Stowe."},{"time":632527,"text":"The story, perhaps apocryphal,"},{"time":634970,"text":"is that President Lincoln invited her"},{"time":637044,"text":"to the White House in the middle of the Civil War"},{"time":639042,"text":"and said to her,"},{"time":640626,"text":"\"So you're the little lady who started this great war.\""},{"time":643290,"text":"And he was talking about \"Uncle Tom's Cabin.\""},{"time":645175,"text":"\"Uncle Tom's Cabin\" is not\na great book of philosophy"},{"time":647706,"text":"or of theology or perhaps not even literature,"},{"time":650850,"text":"but it does a great job"},{"time":653365,"text":"of getting people to put themselves in the shoes"},{"time":655863,"text":"of people they wouldn't otherwise be in the shoes of,"},{"time":658196,"text":"put themselves in the shoes of slaves."},{"time":660598,"text":"And that could well have been a catalyst"},{"time":662379,"text":"for great social change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663983,"text":"More recently, looking at America"},{"time":666345,"text":"in the last several decades,"},{"time":669414,"text":"there's some reason to believe\nthat shows like \"The Cosby Show\""},{"time":672563,"text":"radically changed American attitudes\ntowards African-Americans,"},{"time":675251,"text":"while shows like \"Will and Grace\" and \"Modern Family\""},{"time":678234,"text":"changed American attitudes"},{"time":679597,"text":"towards gay men and women."},{"time":680897,"text":"I don't think it's an exaggeration to say"},{"time":683352,"text":"that the major catalyst in America for moral change"},{"time":686013,"text":"has been a situation comedy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688906,"text":"But it's not all emotions,"},{"time":690322,"text":"and I want to end by appealing"},{"time":691598,"text":"to the power of reason."},{"time":693833,"text":"At some point in his wonderful book"},{"time":695989,"text":"\"The Better Angels of Our Nature,\""},{"time":697212,"text":"Steven Pinker says,"},{"time":699228,"text":"the Old Testament says love thy neighbor,"},{"time":701810,"text":"and the New Testament says love thy enemy,"},{"time":704532,"text":"but I don't love either one of them, not really,"},{"time":707218,"text":"but I don't want to kill them."},{"time":708885,"text":"I know I have obligations to them,"},{"time":710751,"text":"but my moral feelings to them, my moral beliefs"},{"time":714221,"text":"about how I should behave towards them,"},{"time":715934,"text":"aren't grounded in love."},{"time":717981,"text":"What they're grounded in is the\nunderstanding of human rights,"},{"time":719920,"text":"a belief that their life is as valuable to them"},{"time":722143,"text":"as my life is to me,"},{"time":724499,"text":"and to support this, he tells a story"},{"time":726431,"text":"by the great philosopher Adam Smith,"},{"time":728279,"text":"and I want to tell this story too,"},{"time":729965,"text":"though I'm going to modify it a little bit"},{"time":731261,"text":"for modern times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732939,"text":"So Adam Smith starts by asking you to imagine"},{"time":734840,"text":"the death of thousands of people,"},{"time":736741,"text":"and imagine that the thousands of people"},{"time":738781,"text":"are in a country you are not familiar with."},{"time":741020,"text":"It could be China or India or a country in Africa."},{"time":744574,"text":"And Smith says, how would you respond?"},{"time":747058,"text":"And you would say, well that's too bad,"},{"time":749365,"text":"and you'd go on to the rest of your life."},{"time":751241,"text":"If you were to open up The New\nYork Times online or something,"},{"time":753460,"text":"and discover this, and in fact\nthis happens to us all the time,"},{"time":756420,"text":"we go about our lives."},{"time":757941,"text":"But imagine instead, Smith says,"},{"time":760135,"text":"you were to learn that tomorrow"},{"time":761389,"text":"you were to have your little finger chopped off."},{"time":763928,"text":"Smith says, that would matter a lot."},{"time":766097,"text":"You would not sleep that night"},{"time":767508,"text":"wondering about that."},{"time":768861,"text":"So this raises the question:"},{"time":770880,"text":"Would you sacrifice thousands of lives"},{"time":773346,"text":"to save your little finger?"},{"time":775315,"text":"Now answer this in the privacy of your own head,"},{"time":777633,"text":"but Smith says, absolutely not,"},{"time":780552,"text":"what a horrid thought."},{"time":782244,"text":"And so this raises the question,"},{"time":784275,"text":"and so, as Smith puts it,"},{"time":785649,"text":"\"When our passive feelings are almost always"},{"time":787867,"text":"so sordid and so selfish,"},{"time":789315,"text":"how comes it that our active principles"},{"time":790780,"text":"should often be so generous and so noble?\""},{"time":793313,"text":"And Smith's answer is, \"It is reason,"},{"time":795363,"text":"principle, conscience."},{"time":797138,"text":"[This] calls to us,"},{"time":798679,"text":"with a voice capable of astonishing\nthe most presumptuous of our passions,"},{"time":802104,"text":"that we are but one of the multitude,"},{"time":803781,"text":"in no respect better than any other in it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":806222,"text":"And this last part is what is often described"},{"time":808347,"text":"as the principle of impartiality."},{"time":811555,"text":"And this principle of impartiality manifests itself"},{"time":814184,"text":"in all of the world's religions,"},{"time":815951,"text":"in all of the different versions of the golden rule,"},{"time":818209,"text":"and in all of the world's moral philosophies,"},{"time":820663,"text":"which differ in many ways"},{"time":821970,"text":"but share the presupposition\nthat we should judge morality"},{"time":824964,"text":"from sort of an impartial point of view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827949,"text":"The best articulation of this view"},{"time":829771,"text":"is actually, for me, it's not from\na theologian or from a philosopher,"},{"time":832856,"text":"but from Humphrey Bogart"},{"time":834213,"text":"at the end of \"Casablanca.\""},{"time":835760,"text":"So, spoiler alert, he's telling his lover"},{"time":839536,"text":"that they have to separate"},{"time":840676,"text":"for the more general good,"},{"time":842269,"text":"and he says to her, and I won't do the accent,"},{"time":844133,"text":"but he says to her, \"It doesn't take much to see"},{"time":845915,"text":"that the problems of three little people"},{"time":847274,"text":"don't amount to a hill of beans in this crazy world.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":850385,"text":"Our reason could cause us to override our passions."},{"time":853665,"text":"Our reason could motivate us"},{"time":855381,"text":"to extend our empathy,"},{"time":856602,"text":"could motivate us to write a\nbook like \"Uncle Tom's Cabin,\""},{"time":858929,"text":"or read a book like \"Uncle Tom's Cabin,\""},{"time":860652,"text":"and our reason can motivate us to create"},{"time":863346,"text":"customs and taboos and laws"},{"time":865308,"text":"that will constrain us"},{"time":867118,"text":"from acting upon our impulses"},{"time":868794,"text":"when, as rational beings, we feel"},{"time":870383,"text":"we should be constrained."},{"time":871778,"text":"This is what a constitution is."},{"time":873791,"text":"A constitution is something\nwhich was set up in the past"},{"time":876712,"text":"that applies now in the present,"},{"time":878019,"text":"and what it says is,"},{"time":879004,"text":"no matter how much we might to reelect"},{"time":881231,"text":"a popular president for a third term,"},{"time":883834,"text":"no matter how much white Americans might choose"},{"time":885929,"text":"to feel that they want to reinstate\nthe institution of slavery, we can't."},{"time":889997,"text":"We have bound ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891673,"text":"And we bind ourselves in other ways as well."},{"time":894090,"text":"We know that when it comes to choosing somebody"},{"time":896848,"text":"for a job, for an award,"},{"time":899799,"text":"we are strongly biased by their race,"},{"time":902757,"text":"we are biased by their gender,"},{"time":905053,"text":"we are biased by how attractive they are,"},{"time":907268,"text":"and sometimes we might say,\n\"Well fine, that's the way it should be.\""},{"time":909919,"text":"But other times we say, \"This is wrong.\""},{"time":912226,"text":"And so to combat this,"},{"time":914115,"text":"we don't just try harder,"},{"time":916366,"text":"but rather what we do is we set up situations"},{"time":919367,"text":"where these other sources\nof information can't bias us,"},{"time":922406,"text":"which is why many orchestras"},{"time":923721,"text":"audition musicians behind screens,"},{"time":926366,"text":"so the only information they have"},{"time":927610,"text":"is the information they believe should matter."},{"time":930303,"text":"I think prejudice and bias"},{"time":932626,"text":"illustrate a fundamental duality of human nature."},{"time":935720,"text":"We have gut feelings, instincts, emotions,"},{"time":939496,"text":"and they affect our judgments and our actions"},{"time":941657,"text":"for good and for evil,"},{"time":943988,"text":"but we are also capable of rational deliberation"},{"time":947610,"text":"and intelligent planning,"},{"time":949045,"text":"and we can use these to, in some cases,"},{"time":951862,"text":"accelerate and nourish our emotions,"},{"time":953805,"text":"and in other cases staunch them."},{"time":956573,"text":"And it's in this way"},{"time":957807,"text":"that reason helps us create a better world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960574,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":962918,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}